    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Family of the flowering plants consisting of 23 genera and 637 species of short-stemmed, often woody plants distributed throughout tropical, subtropical, and temperate areas of the world. Members of the family have narrow, lance-shaped, sometimes fleshy or toothed leaves that are clustered at the base of each plant. Most species have large flower clusters containing many flowers. The fruit is a capsule or berry.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
